Use **responsive design** with CSS:

```css
/* Base styles for all screens */
body {
  font-size: 16px;
  margin: 0;
}

/* Tablets */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    font-size: 15px;
  }
}

/* Phones */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}
```

Key tools:
- **Media queries**: apply styles at different screen widths
- **Flexible layouts**: use **Flexbox** or **Grid**
- **Relative units**: use `%`, `em`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh`
- **Responsive images**: `max-width: 100%; height: auto;`
- **Viewport meta tag** in HTML:
```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

Example with Flexbox:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}
```

Use **responsive design** with CSS:

- **Use flexible units**: `%`, `em`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh` instead of fixed `px`
- **Use flexible layouts**: `flexbox` or `grid`
- **Add media queries** to change styles at different screen widths

Example:

```css
/* Base styles */
.container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  flex-direction: row;
}

/* Tablets */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}

/* Phones */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .container {
    padding: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

Also add this in your HTML `<head>`:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

This makes the page scale properly on mobile devices.

Use **responsive design** with CSS:

- **Flexible layouts:** use `%`, `em`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh`, `flex`, and `grid` instead of fixed pixels.
- **Media queries:** apply different styles at different screen widths.
- **Responsive images/media:** set `max-width: 100%` and `height: auto`.
- **Mobile-first:** write base styles for small screens, then add larger-screen rules.

Example:

```css
/* Base styles for small screens */
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.sidebar {
  order: 2;
}

.main {
  order: 1;
}

/* Tablet and up */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: row;
  }

  .sidebar {
    order: 1;
    width: 30%;
  }

  .main {
    order: 2;
    width: 70%;
  }
}

/* Desktop and up */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
}
```

Also include this in your HTML `<head>`:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

This makes the page adapt properly on phones, tablets, and desktops.
